<?php	$description = 'Examples on how create a carousel scrolled by letting the user press (a) previous- ,next- or pagination-button(s).';	$keywords = 'user, interaction, examples, buttons, keys, prev, next, pagination, external, links, carousel, jquery';	$title = 'Carousels scrolled by user interaction - Examples';	$script_foo1 = '$("#foo1").carouFredSel({	auto : false,	prev : "#foo1_prev",	next : "#foo1_next"});';	$script_foo2 = '$("#foo2").carouFredSel({	auto : false,	prev : "left",	next : "right"});';	$script_foo3 = '$("#foo3").carouFredSel({	auto		: false,	pagination	: "#foo3_pag"});';	$script_foo4 = '$("#foo4").carouFredSel({	auto		: false,	swipe		: {		onTouch		: true,		onMouse		: true	}});';	$script_foo5 = '$("#foo5").carouFredSel({	circular	: false,	infinite	: false,	auto 		: false,	prev : {		button		: "#foo5_prev",		key			: "left",		items		: 2,		easing		: "easeInOutCubic",		duration	: 750	},	next : {		button		: "#foo5_next",		key			: "right",		items		: 4,		easing		: "easeInQuart",		duration	: 1500	},	pagination : {		container	: "#foo5_pag",		keys		: true,		easing		: "easeOutBounce",		duration	: 3000	}});';	$script_foo6 = '$("#foo6 img").each(function(n) {	$(this).attr("id", "item"+n);});$("#foo6").carouFredSel({	auto: false});$("#foo6").trigger("linkAnchors", ["#links_below", "a"]);';	$scripts = '		<script type="text/javascript" language="javascript" src="../js/jquery/jquery.touchSwipe.min.js"></script>		<script type="text/javascript" language="javascript">			$(function() {				'.$script_foo1.$script_foo2.$script_foo3.$script_foo4.$script_foo5.$script_foo6.'			});		</script>';	include_once '../functies/layout_pre.php';?>				<h1>Carousels scrolled by user interaction</h1>				<p class="no_marg">A carousel scrolled only via the <strong>&quot;previous&quot; and &quot;next&quot; buttons</strong>:</p><?php	$E_script = $script_foo1;	include 'scripts/image_carousel.php';	if ( $showAds )	{		echo '				<div class="adsense_center_728">' . $adsense_balk . '				</div>';	}?>				<br />				<br />				<p class="no_marg">A carousel scrolled only via the <strong>&quot;left&quot; and &quot;right&quot; keys</strong> on your keyboard:</p><?php	$E_script = $script_foo2;	include 'scripts/image_carousel.php';?>				<br />				<br />				<p class="no_marg">A carousel scrolled only via <strong>pagination</strong>:</p><?php	$E_script = $script_foo3;	include 'scripts/image_carousel.php';		if ( $showAds )	{		echo '				<div class="adsense_center_728">' . $adsense_balk . '				</div>';	}?>				<br />				<br />				<p class="no_marg">A carousel scrolled by <strong>swiping</strong> (or dragging on non-touch-devices):</p><?php	$E_script = $script_foo4;	include 'scripts/image_carousel.php';?>				<br />				<br />				<p>A carousel scrolled via the <strong>&quot;previous&quot; and &quot;next&quot; buttons</strong>, the <strong>&quot;left&quot; and &quot;right&quot; keys</strong>, the <strong>pagination</strong> and the <strong>1 - 9 keys</strong>.<br />					All with custom configuration:</p>				<ul class="no_marg">				 	<li>NON-circular and NON-infinite</li>				 	<li>the <code>prev</code> object scrolls 2 items in 750 milliseconds using the <code>&quot;easeInOutCubic&quot;</code> transition</li>				 	<li>the <code>next</code> object scrolls 4 items in 1500 milliseconds using the <code>&quot;easeInQuart&quot;</code> transition</li>				 	<li>the <code>pagination</code> object scrolls during 3000 milliseconds using the <code>&quot;easeOutBounce&quot;</code> transition<br />				 		(number of items depends on to what page it needs to scroll)</li>				</ul><?php	$E_script = $script_foo5;	include 'scripts/image_carousel.php';?>				<br />				<br />				<p class="no_marg">A carousel scrolled only via <strong>external links</strong>:</p><?php	$E_script = $script_foo6;	include 'scripts/image_carousel.php';?>				<p>Clicking <a href="#item2" class="caroufredsel">this link</a> will scroll the carousel to the 3<sup>rd</sup> item. Why? Because it has the class <code>&quot;caroufredsel&quot;</code>.</p><pre class="brush: xml;">&lt;a href=&quot;#item2&quot; class=&quot;caroufredsel&quot;&gt;this link&lt;/a&gt;</pre>				<p>Clicking all the links below will also trigger the carousel to scroll, but those links don't have the class <code>&quot;caroufredsel&quot;</code>. Why it still works? Because the <code>linkAnchors</code> custom event got triggered.</p><pre class="brush: jscript;">$(&quot;#foo5&quot;).trigger(&quot;linkAnchors&quot;, &quot;#links_below&quot;);</pre>				<div id="links_below">					<ul class="left" style="margin-right: 30px;">						<li><a href="#item0">Scroll to &quot;basketballers&quot;.</a></li>						<li><a href="#item1">Scroll to &quot;tree on beach&quot;.</a></li>						<li><a href="#item2">Scroll to &quot;cupcakes&quot;.</a></li>						<li><a href="#item3">Scroll to &quot;hammock&quot;.</a></li>						<li><a href="#item4">Scroll to &quot;New York&quot;.</a></li>						<li><a href="#item5">Scroll to &quot;laundry&quot;.</a></li>					</ul>					<ul class="left">						<li><a href="#item6">Scroll to &quot;mother and son&quot;.</a></li>						<li><a href="#item7">Scroll to &quot;lazy picknick&quot;.</a></li>						<li><a href="#item8">Scroll to &quot;large shoes&quot;.</a></li>						<li><a href="#item9">Scroll to &quot;Paris&quot;.</a></li>						<li><a href="#item10">Scroll to &quot;sunbading woman&quot;.</a></li>						<li><a href="#item11">Scroll to &quot;happy couple&quot;.</a></li>					</ul>					<div class="clearfix"></div>				</div>				<p><em>Note:</em> Set <code>items.start</code> to <code>true</code> if you want the plugin to search for an item-anchor to start the carousel using the url-hashtag.<br />					<em>For example:</em> http://domain.com#startitem</p><?php	if ( $showAds )	{		echo '				<div class="adsense_center_728">' . $adsense_balk . '				</div>';	}?>				<br /><?php	include 'index.php';	include_once '../functies/layout_post.php';?>